<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-387-968  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 387 968.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  June 27 1989 v3 n25 p22(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MacGraphix updated; three add-ons ship. (software packages)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   ComGrafix Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   MapGraphix 2.0 (computer graphics software) (product introduction)MapLink (computer program) (product introduction)MapGrafix Display (computer graphics software) (productintroduction)MapView (computer graphics software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PackagesGraphics SoftwareFile TransferMaps.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Clearwater, Fla.andP;  -- ComGrafix Inc. has released an updated version of itsMapGrafix mapping software as well as three new add-on products.andM;MapGrafix 2.0 adds such capabilities as automated building of polygons andanalysis of polygons and overlays.andP;  Other enhancements to the $8,500 programinclude simplified menus, support for Encapsulated PostScript (EPS) files,improved overlay and symbol directories, and multiscreen support.andM;MapLink, priced at $495, is a file translation package for the conversion ofmap files to and from MapGrafix.andP;  Formats supported include Autocad DXF, U.S.andO;Geological Survey Digital Line Graph and Atlas Graphic.andM;MapGrafix Display, priced at $850, is a runtime version of MapGrafix thatallows users to display and analyze maps.andM;The $495 MapView converts map files among different projection and standardcoordinate systems, including Geographic, Universal Transverse Mercator andState Plane.andM;ComGrafix is located at 620 E St., Clearwater, Fla.andP;  34616; (813) 443-6807.andO;</TEXT></DOC>